events.name: New York Knicks at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 25 points and 16 rebounds, Jalen Brunson scored eight points down the stretch and finished with 17 as the New York Knicks beat the Brooklyn Nets 99-95 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Karl-Anthony Towns and Jalen Brunson carry Knicks to a 99-95 win over the Nets

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 24 points, Deandre Ayton had 22 points and 15 rebounds, and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Miami Heat 116-107 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons and Ayton lead Trail Blazers to 116-107 win over Heat

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes had 17 points and 11 rebounds, RJ Barrett scored 19 points and the Toronto Raptors overcame a 21-point deficit to beat the struggling Orlando Magic 109-93 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes has 17 points and 11 rebounds, Raptors erase 21-point deficit to beat slumping Magic 109-93

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 27 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists for his 19th triple-double of the season, reserve Aaron Gordon was nearly perfect from the floor and the Denver Nuggets beat Philadelphia 144-109 on Tuesday night, extending the 76ers’ losing...
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic records his 19th triple-double of the season, Nuggets cruise to 144-109 win over 76ers

events.name: Washington Wizards at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 21 points, 13 assists and 10 rebounds one day after flying to Atlanta and back to watch a football game on his day off, and the Los Angeles Lakers sent the Washington Wizards to their 11th consecutive defeat with a 111-88 victory...
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron has a triple-double 1 day after cheering on Buckeyes in Atlanta. Lakers beat Wizards 111-88
